  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-11-03",
    "date": "2021-12-17T20:46:20Z",
    "text": "Equine Tax Fairness Act\n\nThis bill modifies the tax treatment of gains and losses from the sale of depreciable property used in a trade or business to eliminate horses from the definition of livestock (thus making the 24-month holding period requirement for livestock inapplicable to horses and allowing horses to be treated as capital assets subject to the existing 1-year holding period requirement for long-term capital gains).\n\nThe bill also makes permanent the 3-year recovery period for the depreciation of race horses."
  },
